   <category name='snake'>

      <section name='examine'>

         <para number='1' comment='ex snake - in habitat'>
         You peer into the large habitat and see a huge snake. It is a shimmering pearl white with emerald green eyes. It is curled lazily on a stone under a warm heat lamp. A cute little sign that looks like two boards nailed to a fence post sitting to one side of the stone reads: "Emerald's Pad".
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='roomex'>
         %s peers into the habitat intently studying the creature within.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='Snake is held by player'>
         You turn your head to look the snake in the eye. Her tongue darts out, flicking you on the nose. Did that snake just grin?
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='roomex - male'>
         %s turns his head to look the snake in the eye. His head snaps back and his eyes widen as the snake flicks him on the nose. Did that snake just grin?
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='roomex - female'>
         %s turns her head to look the snake in the eye. Her head snaps back and her eyes widen as the snake flicks her on the nose. Did that snake just grin?
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='roomex - neuter'>
         %s turns its head to look the snake in the eye. Its head snaps back and its eyes widen as the snake flicks it on the nose. Did that snake just grin?
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='Snake is held by someone else'>
         The shimmering white snake rests comfortably entwined around the body of her current admirer. Her long tongue darts in and out of her mouth, tasting the air.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='roomex'>
         %s peers at the snake as she enjoys the warmth from the body of her current admirer.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='exit'>

         <para number='1' comment='Enter 2327 - turn back'>
         You can tell by Emerald's struggles and evil glare that she wouldn't appreciate being carried around the planet. You should probably replace her in her habitat.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='feed'>

         <para number='1' comment='Feed snake - in habitat'>
         You pull a brass lever beside the glass releasing a small white mouse that somehow looks vaguely familiar into the habitat. As you peer in, the snake quickly strikes at the mouse and coils itself tightly around it until it becomes lost from sight. After a few moments of squeezing the snake uncoils itself and begins to slowly swallow the limp rodent.
         </para>

